This product includes work inspired by and built on top of the following
third-party projects. blight does not bundle their source; it is influenced by
their design and drives one of them as an external dependency.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cwe_checker (fkie-cad)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Design inspiration. cwe_checker (https://github.com/fkie-cad/cwe_checker) is a
static analysis tool that detects CWE patterns in binaries. blight reimagines
the same goal — flagging well-defined CWE classes in ELF binaries — as a
Python-native tool that requires neither Ghidra, Java, Docker, nor a Rust
toolchain. The set of CWE classes detected and the per-binary findings model
are inspired by cwe_checker's approach.

cwe_checker is licensed under the LGPL-3.0. blight contains none of its source
code; the attribution here is for design inspiration only.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
radare2
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Underlying analysis engine. blight drives radare2
(https://github.com/radareorg/radare2) via the r2pipe interface to perform
disassembly, control-flow analysis, and cross-reference resolution. radare2 is
an external system dependency that the user must install separately; it is not
bundled with blight.

radare2 is licensed under the LGPL-3.0.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
r2pipe
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Python binding used to communicate with radare2
(https://github.com/radareorg/radare2-r2pipe). Declared as a Python dependency.
r2pipe is licensed under the LGPL-3.0 / MIT (per its distribution).
